item.title: ++Rep for help
item.dc:creator: @belhelmiel belhelmiel
item.description:
@belhelmiel wrote:

The cache downloader may be broke or you may have put the cache in the wrong folder. Make sure your cache is in (C:) drive folder. If you have LostLegacy then you have to manually download the cache and put it in (C:). I tried fixing LostLegacy’s cachedownloader but when I used a new cachedownloader.java it didn’t work -__- I’m gonna try again while I’m waiting for a reply to my question.
